name: London Girls Club
description:
Red enamel makes this a standout piece.  A red and white enameled silver medallion that reads London Girls Club Union is paired with a vintage saint Milagro.  

The beads are a 12mm White Howlite.


*Milagros are religious folk charms that are traditionally used for healing purposes and as votive offerings in Latin America. They are frequently attached to altars, shrines, and sacred objects found in places of worship, and they are often purchased in churches and cathedrals, or from street vendors.

Milagros come in a variety of shapes and dimensions and are fabricated from many different materials, depending on local customs. For example, they might be nearly flat or fully three dimensional; and they can be constructed from gold, silver, tin, lead, wood, bone, or wax. In Spanish, the word milagro literally means miracle or surprise.
